  "title": "Marketing intern (Finance & Investment)",
  "description": "<p>1. Key Responsibilities</p><ul><li><strong>Marketing Content Creation:</strong> Develop content for digital channels, including social media, email newsletters, and educational investment content.</li><li><strong>Digital Marketing Support:</strong> Assist in managing website content, SEO, and social media platforms to promote financial products (e.g., Unit Trusts, Structured Products).</li><li><strong>Market Research & Analysis:</strong> Conduct competitor benchmarking, analyze market trends, and monitor product performance to assist in strategy.</li><li><strong>Business Development & Lead Generation:</strong> Support client engagement activities, such as seminars, workshops, and client-facing presentations.</li><li><strong>Campaign Support:</strong> Assist in the development and execution of campaigns to promote securities or wealth management services. </li></ul><p>2. Qualifications & Skills</p><ul><li><strong>Education:</strong> Currently pursuing a Bachelor’s or Master’s degree in Finance, Marketing, Business, or related fields.</li><li><strong>Knowledge:</strong> Basic understanding of asset classes, investment products, or financial markets.</li><li><strong>Technical Skills:</strong> Proficiency in MS Office (especially Excel and PowerPoint). Experience with CRM tools or social media management is a plus.</li><li><strong>Soft Skills:</strong> Strong communication, presentation, and interpersonal skills to engage with clients.</li><li><strong>Mindset:</strong> Proactive, creative, and detail-oriented, with an interest in both finance and marketing. </li></ul>",
